     - Decision: DynamoDB as primary Paste datastore over PostgreSQL. Covers the trade-off (Postgres's flexible querying/dev-loop familiarity vs. DynamoDB's fit for point-read-by-ID, serverless ops, TTL, durability, 400KB item cap) and the local-testing resolution (`moto` for unit tests, `amazon/dynamodb-local` in Compose for integration/dev, configurable endpoint env var).
   - **`/Users/yosefshachnovsky/dev/copypaste/docs/adr/ADR-003-jinja2-ssr-no-spa.md`** (created, moved)
     - Decision: server-rendered Jinja2 templates for both create and view flows, no SPA at all. Covers rejection of pure SPA (link-unfurl gap, no JS execution by scrapers), rejection of Next.js (needs a second Node runtime for a page whose complexity doesn't warrant React), rejection of render-at-write-time static generation (couples storage to two systems, harder to edit later). Notes this keeps future mutable-Paste edits simple (just another server-rendered form) and decouples caching-strategy changes from rendering-technology changes.
   - **`/Users/yosefshachnovsky/dev/copypaste/docs/adr/ADR-004-flask-over-fastapi.md`** (created, moved)
     - Decision: Flask (with plain `boto3` and `jinja2-fragments`) over FastAPI. Covers rejection of FastAPI's Pydantic/OpenAPI value (no JSON API exists) and async/`aioboto3` (smaller/less mature dependency, unnecessary at this traffic profile); Flask's advantages (native `jinja2-fragments`/htmx habitat, `Flask-WTF` CSRF/form handling — becoming decisive once auth was confirmed as planned).
   - **`/Users/yosefshachnovsky/dev/copypaste/docs/adr/ADR-005-fargate-over-lambda.md`** (created, moved)
     - Decision: ECS Fargate (behind an ALB, which CloudFront uses as origin) over Lambda-via-WSGI-adapter for hosting Flask. Rationale: Flask's gunicorn worker model doesn't fit Lambda's cold-start-on-scale-from-zero behavior, which would hurt the fast-render requirement precisely on cache-miss requests.
