### Assistant [2026-07-05T12:16:26.163Z]
This confirms a pattern (not a one-off): gunicorn's single sync worker gets stuck on the browser's first connection until its 30s timeout, then a fresh worker takes over and everything works. This is a pre-existing gunicorn worker-concurrency behavior (unrelated to my CSS/template changes) — it'd surface with the original app too. It's a Phase 6 "Compute & networking" concern (worker count/timeout tuning), not something to fix as part of visual polish. I'll flag it as a follow-up rather than scope-creep into it now. Retrying to continue the visual check:

