[tool_call] Write({"file_path":"/Users/yosefshachnovsky/.claude/plans/shimmering-yawning-wren.md","content":"# Pastebin-parity pass: metadata, polish, and small routes\n\n## Context\n\nThe user asked me to browse pastebin.com and make copypaste resemble it as much as possible, flagging anything out of scope. Current templates (`create.html`, `view.html`, `404.html`) are bare, unstyled HTML with only `content`/`created_at`/`paste_id` in the schema.\n\nScope was negotiated interactively:\n- **Auth-dependent features** (login, private/public exposure, folders, \"my pastes\" archive) \u2014 confirmed out of scope. Document only, in `Features.md`, alongside the existing deferred \"Auth\" section.\n- **Title, expiration, syntax highlighting** \u2014 confirmed these don't require auth (they're per-paste attributes, not per-user), and the user approved implementing them now, each with its own ADR/TASKS entry and TDD branch, per `CLAUDE.md`'s methodology.\n- **Visual polish + copy-to-clipboard + raw route** \u2014 approved, schema-free.\n- Explicitly not pursuing: comments, ratings, view counters, ads, social share buttons, categories/tags/folders, password protection, burn-after-read (conflicts with the current `Cache-Control: immutable` design), search, public archive listing, API, browser/desktop/mobile apps.\n\n## New ADR: ADR-006 \u2014 anonymous paste metadata (title, expiration, syntax highlighting)\n\n`docs/adr/ADR-006-paste-metadata.md`, `status: accepted`, covering all three fields as one bundled decision (they're the same kind of decision: optional attributes on an anonymous, ownerless Paste item):\n\n- **Title**: optional string, max 255 chars, stored as the `title` attribute (omitted entirely when blank \u2014 never store `None`/empty string as an item attribute).\n- **Expiration**: uses DynamoDB's native TTL attribute (already flagged as a \"free option\" in `ADR-002`). Stored as `expires_at` (epoch seconds), omitted when \"Never\". Table gets TTL enabled on `expires_at` via `update_time_to_live` (idempotent \u2014 swallow the `ValidationException` DynamoDB raises when TTL is already enabled with the same spec). Since DynamoDB TTL deletion is best-effort and can lag up to 48h, `get_paste` independently compares `expires_at` against the current time and treats an expired-but-not-yet-reaped item as not-found.\n- **Syntax highlighting**: rendered server-side with **Pygments** (new dependency), not a client-side JS highlighter \u2014 this keeps the view route fully server-rendered per `ADR-003`'s SSR/no-JS-framework rationale, and keeps content visible to non-JS scrapers (link unfurling). `language` stored as a Pygments lexer alias string from a curated `<select>` list; falls back to plain `<pre>` when absent/\"text\".\n\n## Schema change\n\nPaste item grows from `{paste_id, content, created_at}` to `{paste_id, content, created_at, title?, expires_at?, language?}` \u2014 all three new attributes optional/omitted-when-absent.\n\n`db.get_paste()` currently returns a bare `content: str | None`. It needs to return the new fields too, so it changes to return a small `Paste` dataclass (`content, title, language`) or `None`. This is a real call-site change in `app.py::view_paste` \u2014 the only caller. This shape change is introduced in the **title** step (first) and reused/extended by the expiration and syntax-highlighting steps.\n\n## Branch/PR breakdown (each its own `step/*` branch off `main`, red-green-refactor, own PR, not merged without approval)\n\n1. **`step/document-deferred-features`** \u2014 docs only. Add title/expiration/syntax-highlighting-adjacent notes are N/A here (they're being implemented); this branch just extends `Features.md`'s existing \"Auth\" section to explicitly mention folders and a public/\"my pastes\" archive as auth-gated, so nothing from today's pastebin comparison is lost. Add `docs/adr/ADR-006-paste-metadata.md`. Update `TASKS.md` with new checklist items for the branches below.\n\n2. **`step/paste-title`** \u2014 add optional `title` field.\n   - Red: `tests/unit/test_db.py` \u2014 `put_paste(table, content, title=\"My Paste\")` round-trips via `get_paste`; a paste created without a title has `get_paste(...).title is None`.\n   - `db.py`: change `get_paste` to return a `Paste` dataclass; update `put_paste` signature to accept `title: str | None = None`, omit the attribute when `None`.\n   - `forms.py`: add `title = StringField(validators=[Optional(), Length(max=255)])`.\n   - `app.py`: pass `form.title.data` through; `view_paste` renders `paste.title`.\n   - `view.html`: render title as `<h1>` (fallback to paste ID) and in `<title>`/OG tags.\n   - Update `test_routes.py`/`test_paste_flow.py` call sites for the new `get_paste` return shape.\n\n3. **`step/paste-expiration`** \u2014 add optional expiration.\n   - Red: `test_db.py` \u2014 a paste written with `expires_in_seconds=-1` (already expired) is not returned by `get_paste`; one with no expiration is returned unchanged.\n   - `db.py`: `create_table` enables TTL on `expires_at`; `put_paste` accepts `expires_in_seconds: int | None`; `get_paste` checks `expires_at` against `time.time()`.\n   - `forms.py`: `expiration = SelectField` \u2014 Never / 10 Minutes / 1 Hour / 1 Day / 1 Week / 1 Month, mapping to seconds.\n   - `app.py`/`view.html`: no visible change required beyond honoring expiry (pastebin shows \"when this paste gets deleted\" \u2014 skip that display, it's cosmetic and not required for parity).\n\n4. **`step/syntax-highlighting`** \u2014 add optional `language` + server-rendered highlighting.\n   - Add `pygments` to `pyproject.toml` dependencies.\n   - Red: `test_db.py` round-trips `language`; a small render-layer test confirms `pygments.highlight` output appears in the view page for a known language and a plain `<pre>` fallback is used when `language` is absent/`\"text\"`.\n   - `forms.py`: `language = SelectField` with a curated list (Plain Text, Python, JavaScript, Bash, JSON, HTML, CSS, SQL, YAML, Markdown) mapped to Pygments lexer aliases.\n   - `app.py`/`view.html`: when `paste.language` is set and not `\"text\"`, render via `pygments.lexers.get_lexer_by_name` + `HtmlFormatter`; include Pygments' generated CSS as a static file.\n\n5. **`step/copy-to-clipboard-raw-view`** \u2014 schema-free additions.\n   - Red: `test_routes.py` \u2014 `GET /raw/<paste_id>` returns the exact stored content, `Content-Type: text/plain`, and 404 for unknown IDs.\n   - `app.py`: new `/raw/<paste_id>` route, reuses `db.get_paste`.\n   - `view.html`: small vanilla-JS copy-to-clipboard button next to the raw/download-style links (no server round trip needed, so `jinja2-fragments`/htmx aren't actually required for this specific interaction \u2014 noting the deviation from `TASKS.md`'s original htmx phrasing, since there's no partial page update to perform).\n\n6. **`step/visual-polish`** \u2014 done last, once the final markup (title, language badge, raw/copy links) exists to style.\n   - `src/copypaste/static/style.css` served via Flask's default static folder (no new route, no bundler \u2014 this also closes out `TASKS.md` phase 5's \"identify static assets\" item for CSS).\n   - Dark theme in pastebin's spirit: top bar with \"copypaste\" wordmark, centered card-style form, monospace textarea, styled submit button; view page gets a header strip (title, language, size, raw/copy links) above a dark code block.\n   - Thin test: `create.html`/`view.html` include a `<link rel=\"stylesheet\">` tag (only testable behavior here; no red/green cycle for pure CSS values).\n\n## Verification\n\n- `uv run pytest tests/unit` after each branch's implementation.\n- `docker compose run --rm app pytest` for the full unit+integration suite (needed once TTL/DynamoDB-local interaction matters, i.e. after step 3).\n- Manual check via the Playwright MCP tools against the local dev server (`uv run flask --app copypaste.app:create_app run`) for the visual-polish and copy-to-clipboard steps, since those are UI-only and not meaningfully covered by pytest.\n"})

