### User [2026-07-05T12:01:18.898Z]
why raw route needed ?

### Assistant [2026-07-05T12:01:32.804Z]
It matches pastebin.com's `raw` link and serves a genuine, different purpose than the copy button: it returns the paste's exact original text as `Content-Type: text/plain` with no HTML wrapper, so it can be fetched programmatically — e.g. `curl https://copypaste/raw/abc123 > file.txt`, `curl ... | bash`, or piping into another tool — without stripping HTML tags/escaping or syntax-highlighting markup first. The copy button, by contrast, reads from the rendered DOM in-browser and doesn't use this route at all.

It was in the approved plan as one of the schema-free additions alongside the copy button. If you'd rather drop it (since nothing in the app currently links to it besides the "raw" link itself), I can remove it — your call.

