[tool_call] Write({"file_path":"/Users/yosefshachnovsky/.claude/plans/shimmering-yawning-wren.md","content":"# CDK infrastructure: deploy copypaste to real AWS\n\n## Context\n\n`TASKS.md` phase 8 has one unchecked line: \"Set up deployment of infra and app releases to Fargate via **AWS CDK (Python)**.\" The user wrote this line themselves (deciding CDK as the IaC tool) and now wants it implemented \u2014 \"I want to see this line checked off soon.\" This is the last major piece before the app can run on real AWS infrastructure per `ADR-005` (ECS Fargate + ALB + CloudFront).\n\nThis touches **real, billable AWS resources** (VPC, ALB, Fargate, WAF, CloudFront) in the user's actual AWS account (`150758095463`, already CDK-bootstrapped in `us-east-1` \u2014 confirmed via `aws cloudformation describe-stacks --stack-name CDKToolkit`). Given the earlier incident this session where a stray local `flask run` accidentally created a real DynamoDB table, this plan draws a hard line: **I will write and `cdk synth` the CDK app (safe, local-only, no AWS calls beyond read-only `synth`), but I will NOT run `cdk deploy` without your separate explicit go-ahead at that time**, since deploying provisions real, costs-money, hard-to-tear-down infrastructure (ALB ~$16+/mo, Fargate, CloudFront, WAF).\n\nPer your standing instruction from earlier this session (no stacked PRs \u2014 merge before starting the next), this is **six sequential branches/PRs**, each targeting `main` directly, each waiting for your merge before I start the next.\n\n## New ADR: ADR-007 \u2014 CDK as IaC tool, no-NAT-gateway VPC\n\nFormalizes the decisions already sketched in your `TASKS.md` note:\n- **AWS CDK (Python)** chosen over Terraform/raw CloudFormation \u2014 keeps infra-as-code in the same language as the app, no new tooling ecosystem for a single contributor.\n- **New `cdk/` directory, its own `uv`-managed project** (own `pyproject.toml`/`uv.lock`, separate from the app's dependencies) \u2014 `aws-cdk-lib`, `constructs`, `pytest` as dev dependency.\n- **VPC with no NAT gateway** \u2014 public subnets only, Fargate tasks get public IPs (`assignPublicIp=True`) for outbound (ECR pull, DynamoDB), inbound locked down via a security group scoped to CloudFront's managed prefix list (`com.amazonaws.global.cloudfront.origin-facing`) so the ALB is only reachable through CloudFront, not directly. Saves the ~$32/mo NAT gateway cost for a low-traffic pastebin.\n- **Custom domain/DNS explicitly out of scope** \u2014 CloudFront's default `*.cloudfront.net` domain only.\n\n## Stack breakdown (5 stacks + scaffolding, one branch/PR each)\n\n1. **`step/cdk-scaffolding`** \u2014 ADR-007, `cdk/` project skeleton (`pyproject.toml`, `cdk.json`, `app.py` with no stacks yet), root `.gitignore` gets `cdk/cdk.out/` and `cdk/.venv/`. Break `TASKS.md`'s single CDK line into 5 sub-checklist items (same pattern as phase 3b), one per stack below.\n\n2. **`step/cdk-data-stack`** \u2014 `PastesDataStack`: DynamoDB table matching `src/copypaste/db.py`'s schema exactly \u2014 PK `paste_id` (string), `PAY_PER_REQUEST` billing, TTL enabled on `expires_at` (mirrors `db.py::_ensure_ttl_enabled`). Table name `pastes` (matches `Config.PASTE_TABLE_NAME` default), exported for cross-stack reference.\n   - Red/green via `aws_cdk.assertions.Template` \u2014 e.g. `template.has_resource_properties(\"AWS::DynamoDB::Table\", {\"KeySchema\": [...], \"TimeToLiveSpecification\": {\"Enabled\": True, \"AttributeName\": \"expires_at\"}})`.\n   - Verify: `cdk synth PastesDataStack` produces valid CloudFormation.\n\n3. **`step/cdk-network-stack`** \u2014 `PastesNetworkStack`: VPC (public subnets only, `nat_gateways=0`), security group allowing inbound HTTP only from CloudFront's prefix list, open egress (no NAT means tasks need direct internet egress).\n   - Assertion test: VPC has no NAT gateway resources; security group ingress rule references the CloudFront prefix list.\n\n4. **`step/cdk-compute-stack`** \u2014 `PastesComputeStack`: `DockerImageAsset` built from the repo's existing `Dockerfile` (root context, `../Dockerfile` relative to `cdk/`), ECS cluster in the network stack's VPC, Fargate service (task def env: `AWS_REGION`, `PASTE_TABLE_NAME`; `DYNAMODB_ENDPOINT_URL` deliberately unset so `Config` falls through to real AWS per `ADR-002`), ALB with `/healthz` target-group health check.\n   - IAM: task role needs more than `table.grant_read_write_data()` \u2014 `db.py::create_table` also calls `resource.tables.all()` (`dynamodb:ListTables`, which is **not** resource-scoped, needs `Resource: \"*\"`) and `_ensure_ttl_enabled` (`dynamodb:UpdateTimeToLive` + `dynamodb:DescribeTimeToLive`, table-scoped). All three need explicit grants beyond the default read/write grant.\n   - Assertion test: task definition container has the expected env vars; task role policy includes the TTL and ListTables actions.\n\n5. **`step/cdk-waf-stack`** \u2014 `PastesWafStack`: WAFv2 Web ACL, `scope=\"CLOUDFRONT\"` (must be in `us-east-1`, which matches our region already), one rate-based rule scoped to the create route (POST `/`).\n   - Assertion test: Web ACL has a rate-based rule with the expected limit/scope-down statement.\n\n6. **`step/cdk-edge-stack`** \u2014 `PastesEdgeStack`: CloudFront distribution, default `*.cloudfront.net` domain, two origins/behaviors \u2014 ALB origin (default behavior, dynamic routes) and an S3 bucket + Origin Access Control origin for `/static/*` (this was the phase-5 item explicitly noted as \"deferred until real static assets land\" \u2014 `style.css`/`pygments.css` now exist via the merged `step/visual-polish` and `step/copy-to-clipboard-raw-view` work, so it's unblocked). WAF Web ACL from stack 5 associated to the distribution. `app.py` wires all 5 stacks together with cross-stack references here.\n   - Assertion test: distribution has two behaviors/origins; Web ACL ID is associated.\n   - This is the only stack where `cdk synth` exercises the **full multi-stack app** together \u2014 verify the whole app synthesizes cleanly here.\n\n## What I will and won't do\n\n- **Will do**: write all CDK code, write assertion tests, run `cdk synth` (local template generation, zero AWS API calls that create/modify anything) to verify each stack, run any stack's unit tests via `uv run pytest` inside `cdk/`.\n- **Won't do without separate explicit approval at that time**: `cdk deploy`, `cdk bootstrap` (already done), or anything that provisions/modifies real AWS resources. I'll flag clearly when the code is ready to deploy and ask before running it.\n\n## Verification\n\n- Per stack: `cd cdk && uv run pytest` (assertion tests) and `uv run cdk synth <StackName>` (or `cdk synth` for the full app once all 5 exist) \u2014 both are local-only, no AWS mutations.\n- Final full-app check in the edge-stack PR: `cdk synth` succeeds for all 5 stacks together, cross-stack references resolve.\n"})

